    "pgm_origin_story": {
      "type": "pgm-split-content",
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/shoulder_copy.jpg",
        "image_position": "left",
        "eyebrow": "How It Started",
        "heading": "A Lifetime of Sports. A Body That Broke Down. And Doctors Who Had No Answers.",
        "body": "<p>Mike Boshnack grew up as an athlete. Skateboarding, competitive sports, pushing his body hard — it was his identity. But years of athletic wear and hard living caught up with him. Injuries piled up. A torn ACL led to surgery. The surgery didn't fix it. More doctors. More dead ends. More \"learn to live with it.\"</p><p>He refused to accept that. If conventional medicine couldn't help him — a young, active guy who just wanted to move without pain — something was fundamentally wrong with the approach.</p><p>That search led him to the Egoscue Method, and it changed everything. The premise was simple but profound: most chronic pain isn't about where you hurt. It's about structural misalignment throughout your entire body. Fix the structure, and the pain resolves itself.</p><p>Mike enrolled at Egoscue University in Irvine, California — the same institution that trains practitioners who work with professional athletes and Olympians — and became a Certified Postural Alignment Specialist. He fixed himself. Then he made it his mission to share what he'd found with the world.</p>",
        "background": "white"
      }
    },
